From: Sergey Fedorov <barracuda@macos-powerpc.org>
Date: Wed, 22 Jul 2026 16:21:25 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/6] Gate GCD and IOSurface usage for Mac OS X 10.5 and FSF
 GCC

Grand Central Dispatch and IOSurface only exist since Mac OS X 10.6,
so introduce OWL_HAS_GCD / OWL_HAS_IOSURFACE feature macros and guard
the Mach IPC and IOSurface code with them; 10.5 builds fall back to
SHM-only buffer support. Weakly link the IOSurface framework so one
binary can cover both.

Also switch OwlMIG from the block-based libdispatch API to the
function-based one (dispatch_source_set_event_handler_f): FSF GCC
does not support blocks at all, and this way the GCD code builds
with any compiler that has a 10.6 SDK.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
